headline: Lyft taps drivers for strategic input to help navigate robotaxi rollout
summary: While robotaxis promise increased efficiency and lower costs, they also threaten the livelihoods of gig workers who rely on platforms like Lyft and larger rival Uber  for income.  The inaugural session will include six to eight Atlanta-based drivers and coincide with Lyft's upcoming autonomous ride launch with May Mobility this summer in the city.  Waymo has expanded its fully autonomous ride service in Phoenix and San Francisco, while Uber has partnered with several self-driving technology companies to operate driverless taxis in some markets.

headline: $357.1 Bn Ride Hailing Market Opportunities and Strategies, 2019-2024, 2029F, 2034F | Innovative Water Ride-Hailing and Driver-Passenger Matching Technology to Revolutionize Market
summary: The global ride hailing market reached $150.34 billion in 2024, predicted to grow to $235.73 billion by 2029. Key drivers include smartphone use and urbanization. Asia-Pacific leads in market share, with significant growth in Africa and Asia-Pacific. E-hailing and two-wheelers are rising segments, while four-wheelers remain dominant. Top players include Uber and Didi Chuxing. Strategic partnerships and innovations like water ride-hailing and advanced app features are driving industry evolution.
